@node "MAIN" "Welcome to 32se onliner!"
  @{JCENTER}@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/32seonliner.png"}@{JLEFT}
  ------------------------------------------------------------------------
  0008 21.06.2026  @{fg shine}32se onliner !@{fg text}                    Tracker Music @{"on" SYSTEM "hip files/mod.module"} @{"off" SYSTEM "hip quit"}
  ------------------------------------------------------------------------
    (Cabal - tracker module by Pierre Eric Laurio/Ocean Software - 1989)
  @{" Thanks! " LINK "TFR"}                                                       @{" Tips! " LINK "NIT"}
                
                @{fg shine}Welcome to eigth issue of 32se onliner! ;)@{fg text}
      
             
                               LET'S DO IT !!! 
  
                                             
@{JCENTER}@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/amigaicon.png"}@{" SCREAM WITH ME: Amigaaaaaaa! " SYSTEM "play16 files/amigaaaaaa2.wav"}
@{JLEFT}    
    SIDENOTE:
    This is just my opiniums my feelings, you absolutely do not need to
    agree in anything and 32se onliner is not a news mag and be kind ;)


@{JCENTER}
@{FG shine}
*** ***
*********
*********
*******
*****
*
@{FG text}


First up... Amiga HW !!!

I'm always in the hunt for the best Amiga HW without breaking the bank
I think this solution is the best at the moment, it gives you options
I'm a power user, I need a fast Amiga.. this has the PiStorm option by
a switch and that's really cool !


AmiCube AGA, I'm looking forward for this great Amiga !!!

So what makes this special ?

It has the mandatory AGA chipset recreated in harware level,
no emulation !

A FPGA with a CPU slot, this makes AmiCube really unique..
Use a real CPU or drop in a Pi-Storm on a 16-bit CPU slot, 
however solution is not the best in my opinium, if it had the 
A1200 32-bit expansion slot it would make it a killer !
This is still way better than nothing ;) maybe that is the
natural evolution at the end ?


@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/amicube.png"}
Ranko has a video showcasing his AmiCube AGA on YouTube !


My take... put AmiCube inside THEA1200 and remove SingelBoardComputer
Maybe I'm too early on this, maybe SBC is very well done and gives
you options like a really fast Amiga etc. 


@{JCENTER}
@{FG shine}
*** ***
*********
*********
*******
*****
*
@{FG text}


AmigaOS 32se update !

This is a first test and evaluation !
I've been thinking about this for years, now it's time figure it out.

 
@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/32se_8c.png"}
You run the updater and after reboot you get the latest news/changes
displayed in a nice AmigaGuide

Be patient and wait for the automatic reboot

@{" v8.85 Updater " SYSTEM "c:execute install1script"}
Show updater icon

@{FG shine}
*** ***
*********
*********
*******
*****
*
@{FG text}


Amiga community is strong and things are moving, I have a hope that
Commodore/Amiga(Cloanto) is todo Amiga HW ;) There is a communication
but it's too early for anything.

 
Summer is here, It's hard to play with the Amiga at 29,6 Celcius
                                                               .
